<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<document>
    <properties>
        <title>jBpm Cartridge Modeling</title>
    </properties>
    <body>
        <section name="jBpm Cartridge Modeling">
            <p>
    			The page describes the modeling standards one must follow to in order
    			to use the jBpm Cartridge.
            </p>
            <p>
                Most of the model elements will require a stereotype to be processed correctly, below you will find
                a table indicating on which model element you may put what stereotype, it will also
                denote which effect this has on the generation process.
            </p>
            <subsection name="Supported Stereotypes">
                <table>
                    <tr>
                        <th>Stereotype</th>
                        <th>Model element</th>
                        <th>Description</th>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Business Process</td>
                        <td>UseCase</td>
                        <td>Putting this stereotype on a usecase will tell the cartridge to generate
                            code from it.
                        </td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Before Signal</td>
                        <td>Call Event</td>
                        <td>Designates an event to be a jBpm <i>after signal</i>, this means it will be
                            calling an <i>action handler</i>.
                        </td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>After Signal</td>
                        <td>Call Event</td>
                        <td>Designates an event to be a jBpm <i>before signal</i>, this means it will be
                            calling an <i>action handler</i>.
                        </td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Node Enter</td>
                        <td>Call Event</td>
                        <td>Designates an event to be a jBpm <i>node enter</i>, this means it will be
                            calling an <i>action handler</i>.
                        </td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Node Leave</td>
                        <td>Call Event</td>
                        <td>Designates an event to be a jBpm <i>node leave</i>, this means it will be
                            calling an <i>action handler</i>.
                        </td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Task</td>
                        <td>Call Event</td>
                        <td>will render the action as a task</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Timer</td>
                        <td>Call Event</td>
                        <td>will render a timed action handler for this action</td>
                    </tr>
                </table>
            </subsection>

            <subsection name="Supported Tagged Values">
                <table>
                    <tr>
                        <th>Stereotype</th>
                        <th>Model element</th>
                        <th>Description</th>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>@andromda.process.jbpm.assigment.expression</td>
                        <td>Swimlane (aka Partition)</td>
                        <td>By using one or more of these tagged values on a swimlane the cartridge will
                            generate assignment expressions into the swimlane declaration in the beginning
                            of the process definition XML descriptor.
                        </td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>@andromda.process.jbpm.timer.duedate</td>
                        <td>Call-event with the <![CDATA[<<Timer>>]]> stereotype</td>
                        <td>Sets the due date for this timer, you'll need to respect the duedate
                            format as defined in jBpm
                        </td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>@andromda.process.jbpm.timer.repeat</td>
                        <td>Call-event with the <![CDATA[<<Timer>>]]> stereotype</td>
                        <td>the number of times to repeat the timer execution</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>@andromda.process.jbpm.timer.transition</td>
                        <td>Call-event with the <![CDATA[<<Timer>>]]> stereotype</td>
                        <td>the transition to take when the timer finishes execution</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>@andromda.process.jbpm.task.blocking</td>
                        <td>Call-event with the <![CDATA[<<Task>>]]> stereotype</td>
                        <td>denotes a task to be blocking or not, blocking tasks need to be finished
                            before the process is allowed to continue
                        </td>
                    </tr>
                </table>
            </subsection>
        </section>
    </body>
</document>
